{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Checking the weather app before heading out? You're seeing probability in action. That \"70% chance of rain\" helps you decide whether to grab an umbrella or risk it. Weather forecasts are probability estimates based on atmospheric data.",
      "title": "Your Morning Weather Check"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every insurance premium you pay is calculated using probability. Companies analyze data on car accidents, home fires, and health events to estimate how likely you are to file a claim — and price your coverage accordingly.",
      "title": "Insurance Premiums"
    },
    {
      "text": "Surgeons tell patients \"there's a 95% success rate for this procedure.\" Doctors discuss medication side effects affecting \"1 in 1,000 patients.\" Medical decisions constantly involve weighing probabilities to choose the best treatment path.",
      "title": "Medical Decisions"
    },
    {
      "text": "Netflix suggests shows you \"might like\" based on probability. The algorithm calculates how likely you are to enjoy something given your viewing history. Spotify, Amazon, and YouTube all use similar probability-driven recommendations.",
      "title": "Streaming Recommendations"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every poker player calculating pot odds or blackjack player deciding whether to hit is doing probability math. Casinos design games with precise probability advantages — that's why the house always wins long-term.",
      "title": "Casino Games and Sports Betting"
    },
    {
      "text": "Should you take the highway or side streets? Navigation apps use probability to estimate travel times, factoring in how likely you are to hit traffic based on historical patterns for that time and route.",
      "title": "Traffic and Route Planning"
    },
    {
      "text": "Quality control teams test random samples from production lines. If 3 out of 100 tested items are defective, they estimate the probability of defects across the entire batch and decide if it meets standards.",
      "title": "Factory Quality Control"
    },
    {
      "text": "Financial advisors discuss portfolio risk in terms of probability — the likelihood of gains versus losses over time. Diversification strategies aim to reduce the probability that all your investments drop simultaneously.",
      "title": "Investment Risk Assessment"
    },
    {
      "text": "When you swipe right, dating apps calculate the probability of a match based on profile similarities, location, and past behavior. Your potential matches are ranked by how likely you are to connect.",
      "title": "Dating App Matches"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "When concert tickets sell out in minutes and suddenly appear on resale sites for triple the price, that's demand overwhelming supply. Everyone wants in, limited seats exist, and prices skyrocket accordingly.",
      "title": "Concert Ticket Chaos"
    },
    {
      "text": "Notice how strawberries cost half as much in summer? Farmers harvest tons at once, supply floods the market, and prices drop. Come winter, scarce supply means you're paying premium prices for the same fruit.",
      "title": "Seasonal Produce Swings"
    },
    {
      "text": "Why does a flight to Miami cost $200 one week and $600 the next? Airlines constantly adjust prices based on how many seats remain versus how many people are searching. High demand, few seats — prices climb.",
      "title": "Airline Ticket Roulette"
    },
    {
      "text": "When a new PlayStation launches, stores sell out instantly while scalpers charge double online. Months later, production catches up with demand, and suddenly you can walk in and buy one at retail price.",
      "title": "Gaming Console Launch Day"
    },
    {
      "text": "That apartment in a trendy neighborhood commanding $3,000 rent? Limited buildings, tons of people wanting to live there. The same unit in a less popular area might rent for half because fewer people are competing.",
      "title": "Apartment Hunting Wars"
    },
    {
      "text": "Remember trying to buy hand sanitizer in early 2020? Overnight demand exploded while supply stayed flat. Prices jumped, shelves emptied, and you saw supply and demand at its most dramatic.",
      "title": "Pandemic Panic Buying"
    },
    {
      "text": "Happy hour exists because restaurants have empty tables at 4pm. They drop prices to create demand during slow periods. By 7pm, full crowds mean no discounts needed — demand handles itself.",
      "title": "Happy Hour Economics"
    },
    {
      "text": "Uber's surge pricing kicks in when too many riders request cars and not enough drivers are available. The app literally shows you supply and demand rebalancing in real time through price changes.",
      "title": "Surge Pricing Surprises"
    },
    {
      "text": "Gas stations across the street from each other charge nearly identical prices. If one raised prices significantly, demand would shift to the competitor. The market forces them toward equilibrium.",
      "title": "Gas Station Price Wars"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Standing between two mirrors in a dressing room? That infinite hallway of reflections is recursion in action — each reflection containing a smaller version of the same scene, going deeper until the image gets too small to see.",
      "title": "The Dressing Room Mirror Trick"
    },
    {
      "text": "When you send a link to a friend who shares it with their friends who share it with theirs, that's recursive spreading. Each share triggers the same sharing behavior, branching outward exponentially.",
      "title": "Viral Posts and Chain Reactions"
    },
    {
      "text": "Zoom into a fern leaf and you'll see smaller leaflets shaped exactly like the whole leaf. Those leaflets have even tinier versions. Nature uses this self-similar pattern everywhere — broccoli, snowflakes, coastlines.",
      "title": "Fern Leaves and Fractals"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your company has a CEO who manages VPs, who manage directors, who manage teams. Each level follows the same pattern: one person overseeing others who might oversee others. Classic recursive structure.",
      "title": "The Org Chart at Work"
    },
    {
      "text": "GPS apps find routes by checking: \"Can I reach the destination from here? If not, where can I go, and can I reach it from there?\" Each step asks the same question from a new position until a path emerges.",
      "title": "Finding Your Way with GPS"
    },
    {
      "text": "Matryoshka dolls nest inside each other — open one to find a smaller identical doll inside. The pattern repeats until you reach the tiniest solid doll that can't be opened. That's your base case.",
      "title": "Russian Nesting Dolls"
    },
    {
      "text": "The \"Inception\" movie layers dreams within dreams within dreams. Each dream level follows the same rules but operates at a different depth — exactly how recursive function calls stack up in memory.",
      "title": "Dreams Inside Dreams"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cleaning the whole house feels overwhelming. So you clean one room. That room has sections. You clean one section. That section has items. You handle one item. Big task, broken into identical smaller tasks.",
      "title": "Cleaning the House"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Aquele celular de R$2.999 parece caro. Mas quando a loja mostra primeiro o modelo de R$4.500, de repente o de R$2.999 vira \"ótimo custo-benefício\". A âncora inicial distorceu sua percepção de valor — você nem pesquisou em outras lojas.",
      "title": "A Promoção Irresistível"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seu time perdeu porque o juiz foi parcial, o campo estava ruim, o jogador machucado. Mas quando ganhou, foi pura competência. Você aplica padrões diferentes para explicar vitórias e derrotas — viés de atribuição em ação.",
      "title": "Torcendo Pelo Seu Time"
    },
    {
      "text": "Você lê uma notícia política e pensa \"isso confirma tudo que eu já sabia\". Mas percebe que seu amigo leu a mesma notícia e tirou conclusão oposta. Ambos filtraram as mesmas informações através de crenças diferentes.",
      "title": "Scrollando o Feed de Notícias"
    },
    {
      "text": "Aquela pessoa que te irritou no trânsito é irresponsável. Mas quando você buzina porque está atrasado para buscar seu filho, tem uma boa razão. Julgamos os outros pelo comportamento e a nós mesmos pelas intenções.",
      "title": "O Motorista Que Te Fechou"
    },
    {
      "text": "Você escolheu um restaurante novo e a comida veio fria. Em vez de admitir má escolha, você justifica: \"mas o ambiente era legal\", \"pelo menos tentamos algo diferente\". Seu cérebro trabalha para não admitir erro.",
      "title": "Defendendo Sua Escolha"
    },
    {
      "text": "Depois que o bitcoin subiu, você \"sabia\" que ia valorizar. Mas não comprou. Seu cérebro reescreve memórias para parecer que você previu eventos — o viés de retrospectiva cria falsos profetas de si mesmo.",
      "title": "\"Eu Já Sabia Que Ia Acontecer\""
    },
    {
      "text": "Você avalia candidatos a uma vaga e o primeiro entrevistado era excelente. Agora todos os outros parecem mediocres em comparação — mesmo os competentes. A ordem de apresentação alterou seu julgamento objetivo.",
      "title": "Entrevistando Para Uma Vaga"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seu parceiro esqueceu de comprar leite e você pensa \"ele nunca me escuta\". Uma falha vira padrão permanente. Nos relacionamentos, pequenos deslizes são amplificados em defeitos de caráter pelo viés de generalização.",
      "title": "A Briga Pelo Leite Esquecido"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Cuando tomas antibióticos y no terminas el tratamiento, las bacterias más resistentes sobreviven. La próxima vez que te enfermas, esas mismas bacterias ya no responden tan fácil al medicamento. Esto pasa en hospitales de todo el mundo constantemente.",
      "title": "Antibióticos que dejan de funcionar"
    },
    {
      "text": "¿Por qué los perros callejeros de ciudades tropicales suelen ser delgados con orejas grandes? Generaciones sobreviviendo al calor sin humanos que los cuiden han favorecido cuerpos que disipan mejor el calor.",
      "title": "Perros callejeros del trópico"
    },
    {
      "text": "Los agricultores pelean cada año contra malezas que ya no mueren con herbicidas comunes. Cada aplicación mata a las susceptibles y deja reproducirse a las resistentes. Hoy hay 'supermalezas' en campos de todo el continente.",
      "title": "Supermalezas en el campo"
    },
    {
      "text": "En Londres durante la Revolución Industrial, las polillas claras desaparecieron de árboles oscurecidos por el hollín. Las polillas oscuras, antes raras, se volvieron mayoría porque los pájaros no las veían contra la corteza ennegrecida.",
      "title": "Polillas y ciudades industriales"
    },
    {
      "text": "Los peces en lagos con pesca intensiva son cada vez más pequeños. ¿Por qué? Porque los pescadores atrapan a los grandes, dejando que solo los pequeños se reproduzcan. Los humanos están seleccionando sin querer peces diminutos.",
      "title": "Peces que encogen"
    },
    {
      "text": "En ciudades con palomas, las de colores crípticos sobreviven mejor porque los halcones urbanos cazan primero a las más llamativas. Las poblaciones urbanas tienen patrones de color distintos a las rurales.",
      "title": "Palomas urbanas vs rurales"
    },
    {
      "text": "La gripe que circula cada invierno no es la misma del año pasado. Los virus que evaden mejor tu sistema inmune se multiplican más, por eso necesitas vacunas nuevas cada temporada.",
      "title": "Por qué la gripe cambia cada año"
    },
    {
      "text": "Los elefantes africanos están naciendo sin colmillos más frecuentemente. Décadas de cacería furtiva eliminaron a los de colmillos grandes, dejando que se reproduzcan principalmente los que nacían sin ellos.",
      "title": "Elefantes sin colmillos"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "When you scroll through Instagram or TikTok, algorithms analyze what makes you pause, like, or share. Every interaction teaches the system your preferences, shaping a feed that feels eerily personalized to your interests.",
      "title": "Your Social Media Feed"
    },
    {
      "text": "Netflix doesn't just show random movies. It studies your viewing patterns, completion rates, and even what time you watch. That \"Because you watched...\" row? Pure machine learning predicting your next binge.",
      "title": "Streaming Recommendations"
    },
    {
      "text": "Ever noticed Gmail catching scam emails before you see them? ML models scan millions of messages, learning spam patterns so convincing fakes land in junk instead of your inbox.",
      "title": "Spam Filters at Work"
    },
    {
      "text": "When you ask Siri, Alexa, or Google Assistant anything, ML converts your voice to text, interprets your intent, and formulates responses — all in milliseconds.",
      "title": "Voice Assistants Listening"
    },
    {
      "text": "Google Maps doesn't just show the fastest route — it predicts traffic 20 minutes from now using patterns from millions of drivers. That \"arrive by 5:47 PM\" is ML forecasting in real-time.",
      "title": "Navigation Apps"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your iPhone recognizes your face even with glasses, a new haircut, or in dim lighting. The Face ID system learned your features and adapts as your appearance subtly changes over time.",
      "title": "Face Unlock on Your Phone"
    },
    {
      "text": "When you upload a photo to Facebook, it suggests who to tag. The system learned your friends' faces from thousands of tagged photos across the platform.",
      "title": "Photo Tagging Suggestions"
    },
    {
      "text": "Type a few words and your phone predicts the rest. It's learned your texting style, favorite phrases, and even your emoji habits to suggest what you'll probably type next.",
      "title": "Autocomplete and Predictive Text"
    },
    {
      "text": "Spotify's Discover Weekly isn't random — it analyzes your listening history, compares it to millions of similar users, and surfaces songs you've never heard but will probably love.",
      "title": "Music Discovery Playlists"
    },
    {
      "text": "Apply for a credit card or loan online and ML models instantly assess your risk profile, analyzing patterns from millions of past applicants to make approval decisions in seconds.",
      "title": "Instant Credit Decisions"
    },
    {
      "text": "Amazon's \"Customers also bought\" feature uses ML to spot purchasing patterns across billions of transactions, nudging you toward products you didn't know you wanted.",
      "title": "Shopping Recommendations"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your email app highlights flight confirmations, package tracking, and meeting invites automatically. ML recognizes these message types and surfaces key details without you searching.",
      "title": "Smart Email Categories"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Your retirement account at work grows quietly while you sleep. A $10,000 contribution at age 25 can become $100,000+ by retirement — not because you kept adding money, but because decades of compounding did the heavy lifting for you.",
      "title": "Your 401(k) Working Overtime"
    },
    {
      "text": "That $5,000 credit card balance you're paying minimum on? Interest compounds on unpaid interest, turning manageable debt into a snowball rolling downhill. This is compounding working against you, silently inflating what you owe.",
      "title": "The Credit Card Trap"
    },
    {
      "text": "When Warren Buffett started investing as a teenager, he wasn't just being early — he was claiming extra compounding time that no amount of money can buy later. Time is the secret ingredient that makes modest savings extraordinary.",
      "title": "Why Billionaires Started Young"
    },
    {
      "text": "A savings account offering 0.5% versus a high-yield account at 4.5% seems like a small difference. But over 30 years, that gap compounds into tens of thousands of dollars — the price of not shopping around.",
      "title": "The Hidden Cost of Your Bank"
    },
    {
      "text": "Student loans keep growing while you're in school because interest compounds on the balance. That $30,000 loan can be $35,000+ by graduation day, before you've made a single payment.",
      "title": "Student Loans in Deferment"
    },
    {
      "text": "Posting one video doesn't make you famous, but consistent creators see their audiences compound. Each video brings new subscribers who watch old content, driving more recommendations, creating exponential growth from linear effort.",
      "title": "YouTube Subscriber Growth"
    },
    {
      "text": "Every rep at the gym builds muscle that makes the next workout more effective. Fitness gains compound — that's why beginners plateau quickly while dedicated athletes keep improving year after year.",
      "title": "Fitness Gains Over Years"
    },
    {
      "text": "Learning one skill makes related skills easier. A programmer who learns Python picks up JavaScript faster. Knowledge compounds, turning the first difficult year into a foundation for accelerating expertise.",
      "title": "Skills Building on Skills"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Aquele ar fresco que você respira no parque? Cerca de 21% é oxigênio produzido por fotossíntese. Cada inspiração conecta você a bilhões de plantas e algas trabalhando neste exato momento ao redor do planeta.",
      "title": "Cada Respiração Sua"
    },
    {
      "text": "Seu café da manhã — pão, frutas, cereais — é energia solar armazenada. A fotossíntese transformou luz em glicose nas plantas, e agora seu corpo usa essa energia para funcionar o dia inteiro.",
      "title": "Energia no Seu Prato"
    },
    {
      "text": "A carne, o leite, os ovos? Os animais comeram plantas primeiro. Até o bife mais suculento começou como capim convertendo luz solar. Toda cadeia alimentar tem a fotossíntese na base.",
      "title": "De Onde Vem a Carne"
    },
    {
      "text": "Gasolina, diesel, gás natural — são restos de organismos fotossintetizantes de milhões de anos atrás. Quando você abastece o carro, está usando energia solar armazenada por plantas ancestrais.",
      "title": "Combustível Fóssil"
    },
    {
      "text": "Florestas como a Amazônia absorvem bilhões de toneladas de CO2 por ano através da fotossíntese. Cada árvore derrubada é um regulador climático a menos trabalhando para estabilizar o planeta.",
      "title": "Filtro do Clima"
    },
    {
      "text": "Aquele aquário com plantas? A fotossíntese mantém os peixes vivos, produzindo oxigênio e consumindo CO2. Sem as plantinhas, você precisaria de bombas de ar artificiais funcionando 24 horas.",
      "title": "Aquário em Equilíbrio"
    },
    {
      "text": "Algas microscópicas nos oceanos produzem mais da metade do oxigênio da Terra. Aquela água azul que você vê na praia está repleta de mini-fábricas de ar trabalhando silenciosamente.",
      "title": "O Oceano Respira"
    },
    {
      "text": "Algodão da sua camiseta, madeira da sua mesa, papel do caderno — tudo construído com carbono que plantas capturaram do ar via fotossíntese. Você está cercado de luz solar solidificada.",
      "title": "Materiais do Cotidiano"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Cada vez que abres WhatsApp o Telegram, tus mensajes viajan encriptados de punta a punta. Ni la empresa que creó la app puede leer lo que escribes a tu familia o amigos.",
      "title": "Tus Conversaciones Privadas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cuando compras en Amazon o pagas Netflix, la encriptación protege tu número de tarjeta mientras viaja por internet. Por eso nunca debes comprar en sitios sin el candadito.",
      "title": "Compras y Pagos Online"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tu iPhone o Android encripta todo el contenido del dispositivo. Si alguien roba tu celular, sin tu PIN o huella dactilar solo verá datos incomprensibles.",
      "title": "El Celular en Tu Bolsillo"
    },
    {
      "text": "Gmail, Outlook y otros servicios encriptan tus correos en tránsito. Facturas, contraseñas recuperadas, conversaciones de trabajo — todo viaja codificado.",
      "title": "Tu Bandeja de Entrada"
    },
    {
      "text": "Spotify y Netflix encriptan el streaming para evitar piratería. Mientras disfrutas tu serie favorita, la señal viaja protegida hasta tu pantalla.",
      "title": "Streaming de Películas y Música"
    },
    {
      "text": "Tu contraseña de Instagram no se guarda tal cual la escribes. Se almacena encriptada, así ni los empleados de la empresa pueden verla directamente.",
      "title": "Contraseñas en Redes Sociales"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cuando el médico te envía resultados por el portal del hospital, la encriptación cumple leyes de privacidad médica. Tu historial de salud viaja blindado.",
      "title": "Resultados Médicos Online"
    },
    {
      "text": "Dropbox, Google Drive, iCloud — todos encriptan tus archivos. Esas fotos familiares y documentos importantes descansan protegidos en la nube.",
      "title": "Archivos en la Nube"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "That satisfying moment when your post gets likes, so you check back more, post again, and get more likes? Social media algorithms detect your engagement and serve you more of what keeps you scrolling — a positive feedback loop designed to amplify your time on the app.",
      "title": "The Social Media Pull"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your credit score affects your interest rates, which affects your debt payments, which affects your credit score. Good credit gets better terms, making it easier to maintain good credit. Bad credit spirals the other way. Financial systems loop back on themselves.",
      "title": "The Credit Score Cycle"
    },
    {
      "text": "When you procrastinate, stress builds. Stress makes starting harder, so you procrastinate more. Meanwhile, tackling one small task reduces anxiety, making the next task easier. Your habits create loops that either trap you or propel you forward.",
      "title": "Procrastination vs. Momentum"
    },
    {
      "text": "Forests absorb carbon dioxide. But as temperatures rise, forests burn more frequently, releasing stored carbon, which raises temperatures further. Nature runs on feedback loops — some keeping balance, others pushing toward tipping points.",
      "title": "Climate's Hidden Cycles"
    },
    {
      "text": "You send a text. No reply. You wonder if they're upset. You send another. Still nothing. Now you're convinced something's wrong. Your anxiety about silence creates the awkwardness you feared. Relationships amplify or stabilize based on how we respond to responses.",
      "title": "The Texting Spiral"
    },
    {
      "text": "Each Tesla sold funds battery research. Better batteries mean cheaper, longer-range cars. More people buy them. More sales fund more research. Elon Musk bet on this positive feedback loop to make electric vehicles mainstream before competitors caught up.",
      "title": "Tech Company Growth Engines"
    },
    {
      "text": "Feeling tired, you skip the gym. Less exercise means worse sleep. Worse sleep means more fatigue. Or flip it: one good workout improves sleep, giving you energy for tomorrow's session. Your body runs on loops you can redirect.",
      "title": "The Exercise-Energy Loop"
    },
    {
      "text": "A few businesses open in a neighborhood, attracting foot traffic. More traffic attracts more businesses. Soon it's a destination. Urban development clusters because success breeds conditions for more success — until rent rises and the loop reverses.",
      "title": "Neighborhood Gentrification"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Scrolling Instagram for 30 minutes before bed feels free. But what could that half hour have been? A chapter of that book on your nightstand. A conversation with your partner. Deeper sleep. Your thumb swipes, and alternatives quietly disappear.",
      "title": "The Late-Night Scroll"
    },
    {
      "text": "Your company offers free training courses during lunch. Sounds great until you realize lunch was your gym time. That 'free' skill upgrade might cost you fitness goals. HR never mentions what employees sacrifice to attend.",
      "title": "The 'Free' Work Perk"
    },
    {
      "text": "Binge-watching a series feels like rest. But by episode five, you've spent the energy you might have used to call an old friend, try a new recipe, or finally start that hobby. Entertainment has a shadow price.",
      "title": "Weekend Streaming Marathon"
    },
    {
      "text": "Holding $10,000 in a savings account earning 0.5% seems safe. But with investments averaging 7%, you're quietly losing $650 a year in potential growth. Doing nothing is still a choice with a cost.",
      "title": "Money Sitting in Savings"
    },
    {
      "text": "That unpaid internship builds experience, sure. But it also costs you three months of potential wages, networking at a paid job, or starting your own projects. 'Exposure' comes with a receipt.",
      "title": "The Unpaid Internship"
    },
    {
      "text": "Buying coffee equipment for $200 seems expensive until you calculate $5 daily café visits. But home brewing costs time and cleanup. Baristas know your order — convenience has value too. Every coffee choice trades something.",
      "title": "Morning Coffee Decisions"
    },
    {
      "text": "Free-to-play games charge no money but devour attention. Hours grinding for virtual rewards could be learning guitar, building skills, or earning freelance income. The game costs nothing and everything.",
      "title": "Gaming After Work"
    },
    {
      "text": "Saying yes to one meeting means saying no to deep work time. Every calendar invite isn't just 30 minutes — it's 30 minutes of focus, creativity, or problem-solving that won't happen. Your schedule is a trade-off machine.",
      "title": "The Meeting Invite"
    }
  ]
}

{
  "steps": [
    {
      "text": "Aquele \"só mais um episódio\" na Netflix? A dopamina antecipa o clímax do próximo capítulo e te mantém acordado. O algoritmo sabe disso — por isso o autoplay começa antes de você decidir parar.",
      "title": "O Autoplay das Séries"
    },
    {
      "text": "Cada curtida, comentário ou seguidor novo gera um pequeno pico de dopamina. Por isso você checa o celular repetidamente sem motivo aparente — seu cérebro está caçando aquela próxima notificação.",
      "title": "O Loop das Redes Sociais"
    },
    {
      "text": "Sabe quando você finalmente limpa a cozinha depois de adiar por dias? A satisfação de riscar algo da lista ativa dopamina. Apps de produtividade exploram isso com checkboxes e barras de progresso.",
      "title": "Checklist e Tarefas Concluídas"
    },
    {
      "text": "Jogos mobile oferecem recompensas aleatórias de propósito. Seu cérebro libera mais dopamina na incerteza do que na certeza — por isso \"só mais uma rodada\" vira uma hora jogando.",
      "title": "Jogos e Recompensas Aleatórias"
    },
    {
      "text": "Aquela fome que bate só de pensar na pizza de sexta? A dopamina é liberada na antecipação, não só na primeira mordida. Seu cérebro já está comemorando antes do delivery chegar.",
      "title": "A Antecipação da Pizza"
    },
    {
      "text": "Planejadores de viagem sabem: a expectativa da viagem muitas vezes traz mais alegria que a viagem em si. A dopamina dispara ao pesquisar destinos, não apenas ao chegar lá.",
      "title": "Planejar Férias"
    },
    {
      "text": "Promoções de tempo limitado e contadores regressivos funcionam porque a urgência amplifica a antecipação de recompensa. A dopamina te empurra para o \"comprar agora\" antes que acabe.",
      "title": "Ofertas Relâmpago"
    },
    {
      "text": "Corredores falam do \"runner's high\", mas antes disso vem a dopamina da meta batida. Aquele app que celebra seus quilômetros está hackeando seu sistema de recompensa.",
      "title": "Apps de Corrida e Metas"
    }
  ]
}
